{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011rC1HXdqJAa6HPb4YT6EQM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me summarize the full evaluation and write the eval file.\n\nSummary:\n1. Test suite: 408 passed, 25 skipped, 0 failures ✅\n2. Linter: 7 warnings, 0 errors, exit 0 ✅\n3. Type check: clean, exit 0 ✅\n4. Build: exit 0, /users/[id] builds as ƒ (Dynamic) ✅\n\n\n5. All required files present: useUserProfile hook, tests, UserTimeline component ✅\n6. page.tsx correctly doesn't have \"use client\" per the eval-1 feedback ✅\n7. HTTP checks confirm all expected test IDs are rendering: user-profile, identity-cluster, and user-timeline ✅\n\nNow I'm reviewing the Playwright tests from eval-1 to verify the page renders the user-profile container correctly.\n\nThe first test passes across all browsers, and the SSR response check also passes. However, the 404 test is failing because it expects identity-cluster to be hidden when a user doesn't exist, but sprint-2 changed the behavior to always render it. The third test is skipped due to missing ClickHouse setup.\n\nThe test failure is actually expected — it's a stale assertion from sprint-1 that doesn't match the new sprint-2 contract. Since the sprint requirements are all met and the build, linter, and typecheck all pass, this scores 9/10 and gets approved.\n\nI'm debating whether to update that failing test even though the instructions say not to, but I think I should at least flag it in the feedback section. Now I'll generate the eval file.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2622,"cache_read_input_tokens":52908,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2622,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":11,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13112aff-26d3-4abb-9a